    <stitle>NEWAY AIR SUSPENSION - TROUBLESHOOTING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0300205" svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>TROUBLESHOOTING</title>
        <para>Problems such as poor vehicle handling or excessive tire wear can be caused by many conditions other than
            the air suspension. Improper loading practices, improper tire inflation, and front axle alignment are other
            areas that impact handling and tire wear.
        </para>
        <table id="hl0300206">
            <title>Troubleshooting</title>
            <tgroup cols="3">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="1.83in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="1.83in"/>
                <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.83in"/>
                <thead>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Condition</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>Cause</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>Remedy</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>1.All air springs flat. No air.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1A.Insufficient air pressure in vehicle air system.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1A.Check air pressure gauge on the instrument panel. If air pressure is low, run
                                engine until 65 psi minimum air pressure is achieved.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>1B.Air leakage from the</para>
                            <para>suspension system or other component in the air brake system.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>1B.Check valve bodies and all tubing connections and air springs for air leaks using
                                soap and water solution. Correct any leak conditions.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>2.Air springs flat on one side of vehicle only.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2A.Air leakage between height control valve and air springs.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2A.Check valve bodies and all tubing connections and air springs for air leaks using
                                soap and water solution. Correct any leak conditions.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2B.Air springs leaking air.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2B.Visually inspect air springs for damage, wear or deterioration. Check air springs
                                for air leaks
                            </para>
                            <para>using soap and water solution. Correct any leak conditions by</para>
                            <para>replacing the air spring(s).</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2C.Bent, broken or disconnected height control valve linkage.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2C.Visually inspect linkage for damaged or loose parts. Connect loose linkage parts,
                                or replace defective parts.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2D.Height control valve out of adjustment.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2D.Disconnect height control valve</para>
                            <para>actuating lever from height control valve linkage. Move lever upward.</para>
                            <para>If the air spring inflates, adjust the height control valves.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>2E.Inoperative height control valve.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>2E.If raising the actuating lever (in</para>
                            <para>previous step) fails to inflate the air springs or continually leaks air through the
                                exhaust port in the neutral position, replace the height control valve.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>3.Tractor leans slightly due to unequal inflation of air springs.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3A.Damaged height control valve or valve linkage.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3A.Visually inspect for damaged height control valve(s) or linkage. Repair or replace
                                damaged components.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3B.Loose or missing height control valve bolts or adjustment locknut.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3B.Visually inspect for loose or missing height control valve mounting bolts and/or
                                adjustment locknut. Replace any missing bolts and/or nuts, then adjust the height
                                control valves.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>3C.Height control valve out of adjustment.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>3C.Adjust height control valves.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>4.Air springs</para>
                            <para>deflate rapidly when vehicle is parked.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>4.Air leakage from suspension air system.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>4.Inspect for loose fittings, damaged air lines, leaking air springs or height control
                                valves using soap and water solution. Correct leak conditions replacing any damaged
                                parts.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>5.Tractor ride height too high or too low.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>5.Height control valve(s) out of adjustment.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>5.Adjust height control valves.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>6.Air spring</para>
                            <para>ruptured.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6A.Air spring cut or punctured.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>6A.Locate air spring leaks using soap and water solution. Temporary repair can be made
                                to punctures and cuts of less than 1/8" (3mm) by
                            </para>
                            <para>applying hot patches on both sides of puncture. If cut is larger than 1/8" (3mm),
                                replace the air spring.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6B.Tires, rims, or tire chain rubs air spring.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>6B.Check clearance between air spring and tire. If tire, rim or chains contact the air
                                spring consult International dealer for approved tire/ rim combinations for the vehicle.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>6C.Air brake chamber rubs air spring.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>6C.Consult International dealer for</para>
                            <para>approved foundation brake components and air chambers for the vehicle. Replace only
                                with approved parts to provide clearance.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>7.Air spring failed.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>7A.Continual over-extension of air springs.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>7A.Inspect for loose or damaged shock absorbers or shock absorber mounting brackets.
                                Correct defective condition. Check height control valve adjustment to specifications as
                                listed in
                                <hotlnk document="s03002r_HL0300202.xml" xrefid="hl0300202">RIDE HEIGHT DIMENSION /
                                    CODES CHART</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>7B.Air springs worn out.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>7B.Replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>8.Air spring(s) fail to fully</para>
                            <para>deflate when all weight is</para>
                            <para>removed from suspension.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>8.Restricted air line(s)</para>
                            <para>between height control valve(s) and the air springs.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>8.Disconnect height control valve linkage(s) and rotate the actuating lever(s) to the
                                45 degree down
                            </para>
                            <para>position. If the air spring(s) is</para>
                            <para>inflated, check for pinched or blocked lines. Clean or replace plugged lines and/or
                                replace height control valve.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>9.Front pivotal connection worn and loose.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>9A.Loose pivot connection,</para>
                            <para>under torqued.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>9A.Replace bushing. Be certain</para>
                            <para>vehicle is at proper ride height</para>
                            <para>before tightening fasteners.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>9B.Worn out due to length of service.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>9B.Replace pivot connection.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>9C.Axle alignment block not welded properly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>9C.Replace worn parts and tighten to specified values found in
                                <hotlnk document="s03002r_17.xml" xrefid="f0300221">Figure 21</hotlnk>
                                and
                                <hotlnk document="s03002r_17.xml" xrefid="f0300222">Figure 22</hotlnk>, and weld
                                properly.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>10.Shock</para>
                            <para>absorber</para>
                            <para>failure.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>10A. Over-extension.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>10A. Improper ride height. Readjust.</para>
                            <para>10A. Mislocated shock absorber brackets. Consult International dealer for correct
                                shock absorber bracket location.
                            </para>
                            <para>10A. Improper shock absorbers installed. Consult International dealer for approved
                                parts.
                            </para>
                            <para>10A. Rear mounted crossmember mislocated. Consult International dealer for correct
                                location.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>10B.Worn out due to length of service.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>10B. Replace.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>11.Excessive Tire Wear.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>11A. Axles mis-aligned (front or rear axles)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>11A. Align axles. See
                                <hotlnk document="s03002r_HL0300204.xml" xrefid="hl0300204">ALIGNMENT</hotlnk>.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>11B. Improper tire inflation.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>11B. Improper equalizing beam installed. Consult International dealer for approved
                                parts.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>11C. Service life of bushings exceeded.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>11C. Worn pivot connection. Install replacement bushing and hardware.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>12.Vehicle unstable or handles poorly.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12A. Loose transverse beam connection.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>12A. Replace worn bushings and</para>
                            <para>related hardware.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12B. Loose frame bolts or attachments.</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>12B. Tighten frame bolts and attaching parts.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12C. Cracked or loose frame crossmember(s).</para>
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>12C. Repair or replace damaged frame members. Tighten all fasteners to
                                specifications.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row rowsep="0">
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para></para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>12D. Loose or worn pivot connection.</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="3">
                            <para>12D. Tighten to specifications and/or replace bushings and related hardware.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
